1
00:00:10,291 --> 00:00:13,250
ONE MONTH EARLIER

2
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:19,250
I'd like you to do something
about this, Captain.

3
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:22,666
I've seen those symptoms before.

4
00:00:23,125 --> 00:00:24,625
Sheesh...

5
00:00:24,916 --> 00:00:26,333
Happiness.

6
00:00:27,375 --> 00:00:28,625
I knew it.

7
00:00:29,291 --> 00:00:31,291
Have you been making
time to see her lately?

8
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:33,957
I see.

9
00:00:33,958 --> 00:00:37,624
Hmm... I guess we'll ask the guild
for a quest as an excuse again

10
00:00:37,625 --> 00:00:40,290
and invite Happiness and
Cecilia to go with us.

11
00:00:40,291 --> 00:00:41,250
Uh...

12
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:45,250
Could he not just invite
her on a date like normal?

13
00:00:45,541 --> 00:00:47,750
A d-date?!

14
00:00:48,708 --> 00:00:53,125
I have two superiors who can't even
ask the girls they like on a date.

15
00:00:53,458 --> 00:00:54,874
My life sucks.

16
00:00:54,875 --> 00:00:57,458
O-Okay!

17
00:00:57,916 --> 00:01:01,790
Operation Go on a Group Date as
a Drastic Measure to Help Raven...

18
00:01:01,791 --> 00:01:03,500
is underway!

19
00:02:36,875 --> 00:02:38,166
Sunny day.

20
00:02:38,666 --> 00:02:40,832
Isn't the weather just lovely?

21
00:02:40,833 --> 00:02:43,957
Let's do our best to
have lots of fun today!

22
00:02:43,958 --> 00:02:47,791
Hey, Duke, since when were
you and Irene a thing?

23
00:02:48,125 --> 00:02:51,207
When I said we were giving
the captain a break,

24
00:02:51,208 --> 00:02:53,083
she said she wanted to help.

25
00:02:53,208 --> 00:02:55,249
I'm so excited! I hope we
find something good to eat!

26
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:57,958
All right, we're heading out now.

27
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:01,208
So where are we headed, anyway?

28
00:03:01,541 --> 00:03:03,749
There's someplace Happiness wants to go.

29
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,500
We're starting with that.

30
00:03:05,791 --> 00:03:06,499
Dying to.

31
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,374
WHERE?

32
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:10,415
Oh, you mean the famous spot
that just opened recently?

33
00:03:10,416 --> 00:03:11,625
You nailed it.

34
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:15,375
A famous spot that just
opened? You don't mean...

35
00:03:18,458 --> 00:03:21,125
LET'S GO TO A BAKERY.

36
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:22,125
Refuse.

37
00:03:23,583 --> 00:03:24,290
LET'S GET LUNCH!

38
00:03:24,291 --> 00:03:25,541
Too early.

39
00:03:33,708 --> 00:03:35,582
That place will probably be crowded,

40
00:03:35,583 --> 00:03:38,958
and if we go there, it
could lead to chaos.

41
00:03:39,083 --> 00:03:40,666
Let's not do that today.

42
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:42,875
Break free!

43
00:03:53,541 --> 00:03:55,582
Wow...

44
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:57,541
This looks amazing!

45
00:03:58,125 --> 00:04:02,041
The king made it to celebrate
the Demon King's defeat.

46
00:04:04,291 --> 00:04:05,541
Identical.

47
00:04:05,708 --> 00:04:08,541
PLEASE DON'T LOOK.

48
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,916
Don't be modest.

49
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:13,083
I'm proud.

50
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,250
Looks like it's going well.

51
00:04:25,541 --> 00:04:27,916
The plan's clearly a success.

52
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:32,041
Happiness, you have cream on your cheek.

53
00:04:32,375 --> 00:04:33,625
Captain?

54
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:38,749
It is the captain.

55
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:41,083
But that voice we just heard...

56
00:04:41,208 --> 00:04:42,416
Right?

57
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:46,249
I see. So sorry.

58
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:49,332
This is the first time
we've heard your voice,

59
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:52,208
so we were a bit surprised.

60
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:57,625
Rude!

61
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:01,915
Vice Captain, good to see you.

62
00:05:01,916 --> 00:05:04,041
The captain's off duty today,

63
00:05:04,166 --> 00:05:07,041
so don't worry about him. You
can continue your patrol.

64
00:05:07,166 --> 00:05:11,875
Hah! He has not only his subordinate,
but a fragile girl defending him?

65
00:05:13,666 --> 00:05:16,624
Please, go ahead and enjoy your day off,

66
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:18,208
"Sir Raven."

67
00:05:24,666 --> 00:05:26,916
Um... Captain?

68
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:28,333
Raven...

69
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:36,207
Hey! Raven!

70
00:05:36,208 --> 00:05:37,790
I'll bring him right back!

71
00:05:37,791 --> 00:05:39,250
I'll go with you!

72
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:46,040
I don't blame him for being shocked,
but I didn't think he'd run away.

73
00:05:46,041 --> 00:05:50,165
There were always some knights who didn't
like having a captain who didn't talk.

74
00:05:50,166 --> 00:05:54,458
It was the vice captain who brought
them all together as a faction.

75
00:05:55,375 --> 00:05:57,000
I'm still a rookie,

76
00:05:57,541 --> 00:05:59,791
so there's only so much I
can do to stick up for him.

77
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:02,708
You've got it harder than I thought.

78
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:05,375
Over there!

79
00:06:08,875 --> 00:06:11,290
This game of tag is over.

80
00:06:11,291 --> 00:06:13,041
Let's head back to the others.

81
00:06:13,541 --> 00:06:15,874
What's going to happen if I go back?

82
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:16,958
What?!

83
00:06:17,375 --> 00:06:20,165
You're running away because
you got embarrassed?

84
00:06:20,166 --> 00:06:22,957
So you never want to see
Happiness again, then?

85
00:06:22,958 --> 00:06:24,333
That's...

86
00:06:24,666 --> 00:06:28,125
I thought I was fine with it
as long as Happiness was happy.

87
00:06:28,541 --> 00:06:30,041
What a letdown.

88
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:35,125
If you still insist on keeping
silent, I guess it is what it is.

89
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:37,333
He's all yours from here.

90
00:06:41,666 --> 00:06:43,291
What's really wrong?

91
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:48,875
Lately, I've been reminded of
my own weakness and powerlessness.

92
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:51,791
You remember that quest
we did at the ocean?

93
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:57,750
That day, Happiness told
me she had a secret.

94
00:06:59,166 --> 00:07:01,416
She seemed to be afraid of something,

95
00:07:01,958 --> 00:07:04,166
so it must be a really big deal.

96
00:07:06,166 --> 00:07:09,916
But how can I accept
whatever her secret is

97
00:07:10,375 --> 00:07:13,125
when all I ever do is worry and fret?

98
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:15,958
It's the same with my voice.

99
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:18,791
All I've done is run from it.

100
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:20,791
If only I could

101
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:24,832
have the courage to approach
the girl I love, like you do...

102
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:25,958
Say what?!

103
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:29,790
Just who do you think I am?

104
00:07:29,791 --> 00:07:32,041
I went out alone with the girl I love,

105
00:07:32,166 --> 00:07:35,582
but I'm such a shy loser, I had
to wear a mask the whole time!

106
00:07:35,583 --> 00:07:38,041
On your feet, Raven!

107
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:41,874
Those legs aren't just for
show, are they?! Hell no!

108
00:07:41,875 --> 00:07:44,458
I know you're not that weak!

109
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:45,790
How do I know?

110
00:07:45,791 --> 00:07:48,000
Because I, like Duke and Happiness,

111
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:50,625
have faith in you!

112
00:07:52,791 --> 00:07:57,125
That bizarre mood you create
always cheers me up somehow.

113
00:08:01,791 --> 00:08:03,416
I'm sorry, everyone.

114
00:08:08,083 --> 00:08:10,833
I'm sorry I acted selfishly.

115
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:13,375
Forgiven.

116
00:08:17,666 --> 00:08:20,791
Okay, now that the captain's
game of tag is over,

117
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:23,624
we're going shopping next!

118
00:08:23,625 --> 00:08:25,625
I can't wait!

119
00:08:30,125 --> 00:08:31,166
Happiness...

120
00:08:32,166 --> 00:08:34,166
I know you can't rely on me now,

121
00:08:34,666 --> 00:08:37,916
but I'll try harder so you can
entrust me with your secret one day.

122
00:08:39,708 --> 00:08:40,916
Acknowledged.

123
00:08:41,916 --> 00:08:44,374
A FEW DAYS LATER

124
00:08:44,375 --> 00:08:45,916
Yoki!

125
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:49,166
What is it, Cecilia?

126
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:52,540
Happiness has gone missing!

127
00:08:52,541 --> 00:08:53,916
What?!

128
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:58,416
Happiness did put in a
request for extended leave,

129
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:01,541
but this note she wrote is so puzzling...

130
00:09:03,625 --> 00:09:06,041
Yep, it's written the way she talks.

131
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:08,415
What does it mean?

132
00:09:08,416 --> 00:09:12,250
It says, "Come find me in
the forest in one month."

133
00:09:12,875 --> 00:09:14,791
What forest is she talking about?

134
00:09:15,208 --> 00:09:18,000
I think I might know.

135
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:22,375
Happiness must have something in mind.

136
00:09:27,583 --> 00:09:29,250
Happy!

137
00:09:30,625 --> 00:09:31,500
Hi.

138
00:09:32,041 --> 00:09:36,165
Man, don't make me track you down
with my enhanced sense of smell.

139
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:37,332
Trust.

140
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:39,375
Everyone's worried about you, y'know.

141
00:09:40,041 --> 00:09:43,333
I've made up my mind, so...

142
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:46,875
I'm going to tell him...

143
00:09:47,708 --> 00:09:49,250
about me.

144
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:51,833
You're sure?

145
00:09:52,875 --> 00:09:57,375
If Raven doesn't accept it,
you could lose everything.

146
00:09:58,625 --> 00:09:59,832
I know.

147
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:04,791
They might want to investigate your
relationship to us and the captain, too.

148
00:10:05,125 --> 00:10:06,499
If that happens...

149
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,665
I won't cause trouble.

150
00:10:08,666 --> 00:10:11,125
This goes way beyond just causing trouble.

151
00:10:11,625 --> 00:10:13,416
Me, Shiek, the captain...

152
00:10:13,916 --> 00:10:17,125
We could all lose everything we've
gained since coming to Minerva.

153
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:21,333
Then again, you're smart,

154
00:10:22,083 --> 00:10:23,833
so I'm sure you know all that.

155
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:26,332
I won't lie anymore.

156
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:28,375
I want him to know.

157
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:35,832
You can do this, Happy!

158
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:36,958
Shiek...

159
00:10:37,583 --> 00:10:40,957
This is really important to you, right?

160
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:43,458
So I'll be rooting for you!

161
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:46,125
You feel the same, right, Duke?

162
00:10:46,458 --> 00:10:47,749
That's right.

163
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:50,499
If that's how strong your resolve is,

164
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:53,125
don't worry about us. Just go and do it.

165
00:10:54,875 --> 00:10:55,875
Thank you.

166
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:58,540
You gotta say something too, Captain!

167
00:10:58,541 --> 00:11:03,041
But you guys summed it
all up so nicely for me.

168
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,040
I have nothing to add.

169
00:11:05,041 --> 00:11:06,875
Useless.

170
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:10,125
Kidding. Captain...

171
00:11:10,625 --> 00:11:11,958
Thank you.

172
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:25,708
Well, if it isn't Sir Raven.
How are you feeling today?

173
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:27,958
I feel just fine.

174
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:30,208
That voice...

175
00:11:30,875 --> 00:11:32,083
You're being rude!

176
00:11:32,916 --> 00:11:34,666
Why do you call me by name?

177
00:11:34,875 --> 00:11:36,165
Huh?

178
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:37,958
I'm not such a fool

179
00:11:38,541 --> 00:11:42,708
as to let a knight who disrupts
the order with his lack of manners

180
00:11:43,208 --> 00:11:44,708
serve as vice captain.

181
00:11:45,625 --> 00:11:49,208
Wh-What do you mean by that, Sir Raven?

182
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:51,208
You will call me "Captain."

183
00:11:59,375 --> 00:12:02,375
My apologies, Captain.

184
00:12:03,541 --> 00:12:05,416
THAT'S BETTER.

185
00:12:13,291 --> 00:12:15,958
ONE MONTH LATER

186
00:12:16,583 --> 00:12:20,958
It's been just about a month
now since Happiness went away.

187
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:24,916
Do you think she's going to...

188
00:12:25,041 --> 00:12:27,957
It's exactly what you're imagining.

189
00:12:27,958 --> 00:12:32,166
Duke should be taking Raven to
where Happiness is as we speak.

190
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:38,457
I didn't realize that Yoki was here.

191
00:12:38,458 --> 00:12:39,832
Mother...

192
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:43,082
You told him about your marriage
arrangement, didn't you?

193
00:12:43,083 --> 00:12:45,124
– No.
– What?

194
00:12:45,125 --> 00:12:48,749
He has his hands full dealing
with his friends right now.

195
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:51,707
I don't want to give him
more to worry about.

196
00:12:51,708 --> 00:12:56,332
Are you sure? Your future husband
has already arrived in Minerva.

197
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:58,707
Yoki is going to find out eventually.

198
00:12:58,708 --> 00:13:02,124
I only agreed to meet him
per the king's order.

199
00:13:02,125 --> 00:13:05,500
Once I meet him, I'll turn
down the offer right away.

200
00:13:07,541 --> 00:13:09,207
Tell me, Cecilia...

201
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:13,124
How do you really feel about Yoki?

202
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:15,583
Yoki has nothing to do with anything!

203
00:13:16,625 --> 00:13:20,415
Anyway, please don't tell him
about that without my permission!

204
00:13:20,416 --> 00:13:23,958
Hmm... So you do feel something after all.

205
00:13:24,416 --> 00:13:27,333
You're wrong! I just...

206
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:28,666
Silly.

207
00:13:29,541 --> 00:13:31,499
If he really had nothing
to do with anything,

208
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:34,958
you wouldn't want to keep your marriage
arrangement a secret from him.

209
00:13:56,875 --> 00:13:59,000
This is... Happiness's...

210
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,000
Come with me.

211
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:07,833
Where is Happiness?

212
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:14,499
Yoki, I have to kill you.

213
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:18,499
I thought if anyone could accept
her, it'd be you. What a letdown.

214
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:20,291
I could say the same about you.

215
00:14:21,791 --> 00:14:23,749
You're not seriously...

216
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:25,375
There is nothing to discuss!

217
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,333
Explain what's going on!

218
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:37,083
I'm punishing you for hurting
Happiness! Steel yourself!

219
00:14:37,541 --> 00:14:38,416
Wait!

220
00:14:42,291 --> 00:14:44,291
I said wait!

221
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:55,625
What?!

222
00:14:59,625 --> 00:15:01,458
He's stronger than before?!

223
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:22,166
So that's your true identity,

224
00:15:22,583 --> 00:15:23,458
Yoki.

225
00:15:24,166 --> 00:15:27,708
What did you do to Happiness, Raven?

226
00:15:29,166 --> 00:15:30,875
I don't need to tell you!

227
00:15:33,541 --> 00:15:35,124
That is...

228
00:15:35,125 --> 00:15:36,583
enough!

229
00:15:37,666 --> 00:15:40,166
Endless Dark!

230
00:15:52,416 --> 00:15:56,166
Do you get it now, Raven?
You can't beat me.

231
00:15:57,625 --> 00:15:59,041
But I won't give up!

232
00:15:59,666 --> 00:16:01,333
Why are you so determined?

233
00:16:01,875 --> 00:16:04,125
What happened between you and Happiness?

234
00:16:04,583 --> 00:16:06,041
I promised her.

235
00:16:06,458 --> 00:16:10,665
She said you plucked every feather from
her body to disguise her as a human,

236
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:13,125
and she asked me to give
you a beating for it.

237
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:14,333
Wha?

238
00:16:15,666 --> 00:16:16,666
Huh?

239
00:16:16,916 --> 00:16:19,582
That's what's going on. So let's do this.

240
00:16:19,583 --> 00:16:21,124
Give me a break!

241
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:24,666
If you give me a beating with
that sword, even I'm gonna die!

242
00:16:24,875 --> 00:16:27,291
Oh... Well, then, I'll just...

243
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:29,416
use the back edge.

244
00:16:29,708 --> 00:16:31,916
That sword's double-edged!

245
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:44,125
Happiness!

246
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:48,916
Doot do-doo!

247
00:16:50,416 --> 00:16:54,958
A mischievous spirit can
only take you so far!

248
00:16:57,958 --> 00:16:58,958
Apology.

249
00:16:59,416 --> 00:17:00,458
I'm sorry.

250
00:17:02,041 --> 00:17:06,458
And? How did you two...
well... settle things?

251
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,915
Oh, well...

252
00:17:08,916 --> 00:17:11,582
Duke led me to a certain forest, and...

253
00:17:11,583 --> 00:17:13,958
You'll have to go on your own from here.

254
00:17:17,208 --> 00:17:18,083
Duke?

255
00:17:18,916 --> 00:17:23,208
You're gonna have to give
Happiness an answer yourself.

256
00:17:27,666 --> 00:17:28,916
Happiness?

257
00:17:31,958 --> 00:17:34,250
Happiness, are you up there?

258
00:17:34,958 --> 00:17:37,500
Why... are you hiding?

259
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:39,833
Visitor. Gratitude.

260
00:17:40,333 --> 00:17:42,625
Why did you want me to come here?

261
00:17:43,250 --> 00:17:44,750
This is...

262
00:17:45,416 --> 00:17:47,791
where I started.

263
00:17:48,125 --> 00:17:52,250
And... where I ended.

264
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:56,958
So it's a place that means a lot to you.

265
00:17:58,416 --> 00:18:01,374
Raven, I'm glad I met you.

266
00:18:01,375 --> 00:18:03,624
Spending time with you is fun.

267
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:05,750
I'd like to be together forever.

268
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,458
– I also—
– No! Don't come closer!

269
00:18:30,583 --> 00:18:32,208
I was scared.

270
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:34,500
I couldn't keep lying forever.

271
00:18:35,041 --> 00:18:40,916
But... when I thought...
it might mean the end...

272
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:47,833
I'm sorry.

273
00:18:55,083 --> 00:18:56,250
Raven?

274
00:18:57,583 --> 00:19:00,541
I'm sorry I didn't notice.

275
00:19:01,458 --> 00:19:03,791
You've been suffering
over this for so long.

276
00:19:04,375 --> 00:19:06,291
You won't reject me?

277
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:11,249
Of course not. Because I love you.

278
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:13,291
I guess that's not a
sufficient reason, is it?

279
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:15,791
I-I...

280
00:19:17,458 --> 00:19:18,791
love you, too.

281
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:22,958
Then everything's fine, right?

282
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:24,625
Yes.

283
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:35,582
That's so sweet!

284
00:19:35,583 --> 00:19:37,165
That's way too sweet!

285
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:42,499
Sweeter than the sugar
cubes at Cecilia's house!

286
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:45,915
You two had a fairy-tale ending like that,

287
00:19:45,916 --> 00:19:48,791
and you were talking about beating me up?!

288
00:19:48,916 --> 00:19:50,958
All right. I get it.

289
00:19:51,875 --> 00:19:55,540
Let me offer you my congratulations.

290
00:19:55,541 --> 00:19:57,290
Saint Chains!

291
00:19:57,291 --> 00:19:58,624
What's this for?!

292
00:19:58,625 --> 00:19:59,583
Undo!

293
00:19:59,875 --> 00:20:02,666
Oh! I'll put up a barrier
to keep monsters out.

294
00:20:02,958 --> 00:20:05,333
Well, you two have a nice time now!

295
00:20:11,791 --> 00:20:13,125
What a relief.

296
00:20:13,958 --> 00:20:16,833
If, by some chance, Raven and
Happiness didn't work out,

297
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:19,708
we probably couldn't have tea
together like this anymore.

298
00:20:21,458 --> 00:20:22,332
Cecilia?

299
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:23,958
Oh, I'm sorry!

300
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:29,999
Um... I'm going to be a
little busy for a while,

301
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,916
so I won't have much time for tea.

302
00:20:32,375 --> 00:20:34,916
Oh, but it's only for a little while!

303
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:37,333
Oh, okay. Don't worry about it.

304
00:20:37,458 --> 00:20:39,707
I'll be away from Minerva for a while.

305
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:40,665
Huh?

306
00:20:40,666 --> 00:20:44,250
Yuga asked me to help him with a quest,

307
00:20:44,666 --> 00:20:47,499
so I have to go to some mine somewhere.

308
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,750
I... see...

309
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:54,250
He kind of begged me.

310
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:57,208
It might take two or three weeks.

311
00:20:58,125 --> 00:21:01,957
So at some point, you became
good friends with Yuga, too?

312
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:02,916
Huh?

313
00:21:04,208 --> 00:21:05,750
Is Yoki here?!

314
00:21:07,541 --> 00:21:09,582
Give Yoki to us.

315
00:21:09,583 --> 00:21:11,624
Apprehend! Haul in!

316
00:21:11,625 --> 00:21:14,500
Yoki, did you do something again?

317
00:21:16,125 --> 00:21:19,000
They messed with me first!

318
00:21:20,666 --> 00:21:22,083
Thanks for the tea!

319
00:21:26,041 --> 00:21:27,166
I'll come by again!

320
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:30,957
Don't you run away!

321
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:32,540
Annihilate!

322
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:35,250
Honestly... You'd better.

323
00:21:37,791 --> 00:21:39,125
Let's go, too.

324
00:22:05,125 --> 00:22:07,208
Happiness! I'm happy for you!

325
00:22:07,416 --> 00:22:08,916
Congratulations!

326
00:22:12,875 --> 00:22:16,124
It seems we have a debt to
Yoki that we can never repay.

327
00:22:16,125 --> 00:22:18,250
Thank you, Captain.
